Q1. Exception  vs  Error ?
Exception: 
A problem that occurs during program execution and can be handled using try-catch (e.g., NullPointerException).
Error: 
A serious system-level problem that occurs at runtime and cannot be handled by the program (e.g., OutOfMemoryError).


